gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 108, 76ers 96
gameRecap.excerpt: Domantas Sabonis put up his league-leading 25th triple-double of the season as the Kings defeat the 76ers, 108-96. Sabonis recorded 11 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists for the Kings, while Keegan Murray (23 points, three 3PM) and DeAaron Fox (23 points, eight rebounds, five assists) added a combined 46 points in the victory. Tyrese Maxey notched 29 points and five 3PM for the 76ers in the losing effort. The Kings improve to 42-29 on the season, while the 76ers fall to 39-33.
